    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#IndustrialClassification"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "UN international industrial classification used in Peru. Requires manual mapping to GICS/SASB for TNFD assessments."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CIIU"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CIIU (UN international classification used in Peru) does not map automatically to GICS or SASB/SICS sectors required for ENCORE-based TNFD assessments."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Clasificación Industrial Internacional Uniforme"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasAmbiguity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CIIUtoGICSAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasBridgingCondition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A lossy correspondence requires manual alignment of CIIU codes to GICS and SASB/SICS sectors, with documentation of ambiguous cases. Performed by Santander Peru during LEAP L1 scoping."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#incommensurableWith" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#mappableTo" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CIIUtoGICSAmbiguity",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#SemanticAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Documented semantic ambiguity in the CIIU-to-GICS/SASB mapping required for TNFD assessments in Peru. Peruvian CIIU categories require manual alignment with GICS and SASB/SICS sector definitions."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CIIU to GICS Semantic Ambiguity"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CIIUtoGICSMapping",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#SemanticAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Manual sector correspondence developed by Santander Peru to align its CIIU-classified portfolio with GICS and SASB/SICS sectors required for ENCORE-based materiality screening."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CIIU to GICS/SASB Mapping (Santander Peru)"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CNAE",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#IndustrialClassification"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Brazilian national industrial classification used by financial institutions for portfolio reporting. Requires manual mapping to GICS for TNFD/ENCORE assessments."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CNAE"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CNAE (Brazilian national classification) and GICS (international standard used by ENCORE/TNFD) do not maintain a bijective correspondence. Multiple CNAE codes may map to one GICS sector and vice versa, generating semantic ambiguity in sector-level materiality assessments."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Classificação Nacional de Atividades Econômicas"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasAmbiguity" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CNAEtoGICSAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasBridgingCondition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A lossy correspondence is admissible when each CNAE code is manually mapped to the most representative GICS sector, with explicit documentation of multi-to-one and one-to-many correspondences. This mapping was performed by EY during the CEBDS Brazil LEAP pilot and required significant expert effort. The result is not automatically reversible."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#incommensurableWith" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#mappableTo" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CNAEtoGICSAmbiguity",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#SemanticAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Documented semantic ambiguity in the CNAE-to-GICS mapping required for TNFD/ENCORE assessments. Brazilian CNAE categories do not maintain a bijective correspondence with GICS sectors — multiple CNAE codes may map to one GICS sector or vice versa. Required significant manual effort in the CEBDS Brazil pilot."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CNAE to GICS Semantic Ambiguity"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CNAEtoGICSMapping",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#SemanticAmbiguity"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Manual sector correspondence developed during the CEBDS Brazil LEAP pilot to align portfolio reporting under CNAE with ENCORE/TNFD materiality assessment requiring GICS classification."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "CNAE to GICS Mapping (CEBDS Brazil)"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Caixa",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#FinancialInstitution"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Caixa Econômica Federal"
  } ],
  "https://schema.org/url" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://www.caixa.gov.br"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#appliesFramework" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#TNFD"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#operatesInCountry" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Brazil"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#usesClassification" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CNAE"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Cerrado",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Biome"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Brazilian tropical savanna — global biodiversity hotspot under severe agricultural pressure. 67.7% increase in deforestation in 2023. Under-sampled in GBIF for its specific endemic species."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Cerrado Biome"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#CerradoDataGap",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GeographicSamplingBias"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Documented under-sampling of species occurrence records in GBIF for the Cerrado biome, particularly invertebrates and endemic species. Documented in the CEBDS Brazil LEAP pilot as a challenge for L4 sensitive site identification."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Cerrado GBIF Data Gap"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#affectsFramework" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ESRS_E4"
  }, {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#TNFD"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ConsumerDiscretionarySector",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Sector"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Consumer Discretionary Sector"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#assessedUnder" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#TNFD"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasSectorClassification" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ConsumerStaplesSector",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Sector"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Consumer Staples Sector"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Companies involved in the production or sale of essential products, including food, beverages, tobacco, and hygiene products. Priority 1 in CEBDS Brazil heatmap."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#assessedUnder" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#TNFD"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasSectorClassification" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GICS"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#Country",
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A sovereign country where a financial institution operates or has portfolio exposure."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Country"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.opengis.net/ont/geosparql#Feature"
  }, {
    "@id" : "https://schema.org/Country"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#DataGap",
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A systematic absence or insufficiency of biodiversity occurrence data limiting the reliability of framework-based risk assessments in a given geographic area, taxonomic group or ecosystem type."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Data Gap"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#DataSufficiencyAssessment",
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "An evaluation of whether available biodiversity data from sources such as GBIF and OBIS are sufficient to meet the information requirements of a given disclosure framework for a specific biome, sector and location. Quantifies data gaps arising from geographic and taxonomic sampling bias."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Data Sufficiency Assessment"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#DisclosureFramework",
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A regulatory or voluntary framework requiring organisations to assess and disclose their nature-related impacts, dependencies, risks and opportunities."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Disclosure Framework"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#DisclosureRequirement",
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A specific disclosure requirement within a framework, at the level of a recommended disclosure, datapoint or metric (e.g., TNFD Strategy D, ESRS E4-5, GRI 101-6)."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Disclosure Requirement"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ENCOREData",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#BiodiversityDataSource"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Exploring Natural Capital Opportunities, Risks and Exposure — sector-level tool for screening nature-related impacts and dependencies. Uses a quantitative scale (3-9). Used in L2 by both Santander Peru and CEBDS Brazil."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE Tool"
  } ],
  "https://schema.org/url" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://encorenature.org"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ENCOREMateriality",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#QuantitativeMaterialityScale"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE scores impacts and dependencies on a numerical scale: very low=3, low=4.5, medium=6, high=7.5, very high=9. Used by TNFD for sector-level screening."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE Quantitative Materiality Scale"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE applies a quantitative composite scale (3-9) aggregating dependencies and impacts by production process. GRI 101 applies qualitative impact materiality requiring stakeholder-informed severity assessment. The two approaches operate at different epistemic levels and use incompatible measurement units."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasBridgingCondition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A lossy approximation is admissible if ENCORE sector scores are supplemented with qualitative stakeholder evidence meeting GRI 101 impact severity criteria. The numerical scale (3-9) cannot be directly compared with GRI qualitative thresholds without explicit bridging assumptions documented per sector."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#incommensurableWith" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GRI101ImpactMateriality"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ENCOREScale",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#QuantitativeMaterialityScale"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE numerical scale where 3=very low, 4.5=low, 6=medium, 7.5=high, 9=very high dependency/impact. Used in CEBDS Brazil pilot to produce heatmap weighted by loan volume and client count."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ENCORE Scale 3-9"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ESRSBiodiversitySensitiveArea",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Areas designated for biodiversity protection under ESRS E4, including Natura 2000 sites, UNESCO World Heritage, KBAs, and IUCN Category I–IV protected areas."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ESRS E4 Biodiversity-sensitive Area"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#FrameworkConcept"
  }, {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#TNFDPriorityLocation"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#GRIOperationsAdjacentProtectedAreas"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ESRS E4 biodiversity-sensitive areas are a strict subset of TNFD priority locations. TNFD additionally covers rapid ecosystem decline and high water stress sites absent from the ESRS definition. Treating as equivalent produces false negatives in LAC screening."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Partial equivalence with difference in reference: both concepts cover protected areas and KBAs, but ESRS E4 explicitly references Natura 2000 sites and IUCN Category I-IV protected areas, while GRI 101 uses a broader definition based on IUCN and Ramsar without the Natura 2000 specificity. The equivalence holds for the KBA criterion; the normative reference to EU-specific designations introduces a scope difference."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#definedBy" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ESRS_E4"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ESRSDoubleMateriality",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ESRS E4 double materiality: an issue is material if it has significant impacts on biodiversity (impact materiality) OR poses financial risks/opportunities (financial materiality)."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ESRS E4 Double Materiality"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#MaterialityBoundary"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#note" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "ESRS E4 double materiality requires assessment of both impact and financial dimensions. TNFD applies single enterprise-value materiality. The two boundaries define different populations of disclosable items; thresholds are not interchangeable."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#definedBy" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#ESRS_E4"
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#hasBridgingCondition" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A lossy approximation is admissible if the analyst explicitly assumes that impact-material issues under ESRS E4 are also financially material under TNFD, and documents this assumption with supporting evidence. Does not hold by default."
  } ],
  "https://w3id.org/biodivrisK-onto#incommensurableWith" : [ {
